<!-- These strings are used by Firefox's custom about:certerror page,
a replacement for the standard security certificate errors produced
by NSS/PSM via netError.xhtml. -->


<!ENTITY certerror.pagetitle  "Untrusted Connection">
<!ENTITY certerror.longpagetitle "This Connection is Untrusted">
<!-- Localization note (certerror.introPara1) - The string "#1" will
be replaced at runtime with the name of the server to which the user
was trying to connect. -->

<!ENTITY certerror.introPara1 "You have asked &brandShortName; to connect 
securely to <b>#1</b>, but we can't confirm that your connection is secure.">
<!ENTITY certerror.introPara2 "Sa normal na sitwasyon, kapag sinubukan mong mag-connect nang secure, 
ang mga site ay mag-present ng trusted identification upang mapatunayan na ikaw ay 
patungo sa tamang lugar. Pero, ang identity ng site ay hindi ma-verify. ">

<!ENTITY certerror.whatShouldIDo.heading "Ano ang dapat kong gawin?">
<!ENTITY certerror.whatShouldIDo.content "Kung ikaw ay kadalasang kumkunek 
sa website na ito ng walang problema, ang kamaliang ito ay maaring 
mangangahulugang may nagtatangkang gayahin ang website, at dapat huwag ng magpatuloy.">



<!ENTITY certerror.expert.heading "Nauunawan ko ang mga Panganib">
<!ENTITY certerror.expert.content "Pwede mong itakda sa &brandShortName; na pagkatiwalaan ang website na ito.<b>Kahit aprubado mo ang website na ito, maaaring may tao na nakiki-alam sa connection mo.</b>">
<!ENTITY certerror.expert.contentPara2 "Huwag magdagdag ng exception maliban kung
may magandang rason ang site na ito na hindi gumamit ng trusted identification.">


